    Demo Case 02 - Open / General Inquiry / Medium priority
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the SECOND of the 10-case demo dataset; together with
    case 01 (Draft, the immediately preceding lifecycle state for the
    General Inquiry type) and cases 03 through 10 (which cover the
    remaining statuses across both case types), it satisfies the AAP
    requirement (Section 0.7.4) of "at least 10 demo cases across all
    six statuses and both case types," and contributes to the dataset
    matrix:

        Case 01 - Draft       / General Inquiry
        Case 02 - Open        / General Inquiry / Medium    ## THIS FILE
        Case 03 - In Progress / General Inquiry / Medium
        Case 04 - Pending     / General Inquiry / High
        Case 05 - Resolved    / General Inquiry / Medium
        Case 06 - Closed      / General Inquiry
        Case 07 - Open        / Complaint       / High
        Case 08 - In Progress / Complaint
        Case 09 - Resolved    / Complaint
        Case 10 - Closed      / Complaint

    The 10-case dataset thus exercises:
      * Every one of the six statuses (Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending,
        Resolved, Closed) - this case occupies the Open slot for the
        General Inquiry case type. It is paired with case 07, which
        occupies the Open slot for the Complaint case type. Together
        cases 02 and 07 cover the Open status across both case types.
      * Both case types (General Inquiry and Complaint) - case 02 is on
        the General Inquiry side; case 07 is the Complaint counterpart.
      * Multiple priorities (Low, Medium, High, Critical) - this case
        contributes the Medium bar to the all_cases_by_priority chart
        (paired with cases 03 In Progress General Inquiry Medium and
        05 Resolved General Inquiry Medium, which are also Medium).
      * The Open -> In Progress TRANSITION-GUARD scenario - this case
        is the CANONICAL test input for the validate_inprogress_transition
        subflow's "assigned_agent must be populated AND must be a
        member of assigned_group" gate. With assigned_agent intentionally
        absent on this Open case, any attempt to advance this case to
        In Progress via the form MUST be blocked by the subflow until
        an agent is selected (and that agent is a member of the
        assigned_group).
      * The case_agent's "Assigned only" ACL group-membership clause -
        this case is visible to the demo agent ONLY because the demo
        agent is a member of x_[scope]_demo_team (the assigned_group),
        even though assigned_agent is empty. This is the canonical
        test for the SECOND clause of "Assigned only":
        "assigned_group IN current.user_group_membership" (the FIRST
        clause "assigned_agent = current.sys_id" is exercised by all
        cases that DO have assigned_agent populated, e.g. case 03).

    Lifecycle position - WHY Open / General Inquiry / Medium is
    meaningful:
      A General Inquiry case that has reached Open status has traversed:
        Draft -> Open
      The case was created as a Draft (with subject, description,
      requester_name, optionally requester_email and priority but NOT
      assigned_group), then routed to a queue / assigned to a group on
      the Draft -> Open transition. Per AAP Section 0.5.5's transition
      matrix:
        - The Draft -> Open transition is gated by
          validate_open_transition: assigned_group must be populated;
          otherwise the form-level blocking error is surfaced.
        - The Open -> In Progress transition is gated by
          validate_inprogress_transition: assigned_agent must be
          populated AND must be a member of assigned_group; otherwise
          the form-level blocking error is surfaced.
        - Any -> Draft is PROHIBITED ("Cases cannot be returned to
          Draft." per AAP Section 0.7.4); any attempt to back-
          transition this Open case to Draft MUST be blocked by the
          x_[scope]_block_draft_backtransition Before-Update business
          rule.
      This case occupies the Open side of those gates: assigned_group
      is populated, assigned_agent is INTENTIONALLY ABSENT (the
      defining feature of Open in this dataset; case 07 follows the
      same convention for the Complaint side), pending_reason is
      absent (only relevant on Pending status), and the case has NOT
      yet been picked up by an agent. The Medium priority is the
      canonical "ordinary case" priority - elevated above Low (no
      urgency) but not yet reaching High or Critical thresholds.

