    Key insights (per the agent prompt):
      1. Demo case 02 is the canonical Open case for the General
         Inquiry flow. It exercises the queue-based assignment pattern
         where a case has been routed to a group but not yet picked up
         by an agent. This mirrors a realistic case lifecycle: the
         intake/dispatcher routes the case to a team queue (the
         demo_team group), and the case waits in the queue for a team
         member to claim it via the form's assigned_agent field
         (which then triggers the Open -> In Progress transition
         through the standard state machine).

      2. NO <assigned_agent> is the DEFINING FEATURE of this case.
         This is what makes the Open -> In Progress transition blocked;
         the validate_inprogress_transition subflow requires an
         assigned_agent who is a member of assigned_group. Until an
         operator populates assigned_agent on the form (selecting the
         demo agent who is a member of x_[scope]_demo_team), any
         transition attempt to In Progress MUST surface a form-level
         blocking error and MUST be denied.

      3. The status "Open" has a single capital O. The exact choice
         value is "Open" per AAP Section 0.5.7 and
         ../../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml. Common mistakes to
         avoid: "open", "OPEN", "OPENED", "OPN" - all of these would
         FAIL choice-value validation against the registered choice
         list.

      4. The <assigned_group> reference uses
         display_value="x_[scope]_demo_team" and resolves by name
         lookup against sys_user_group. The element value is the same
         string as the display_value (NOT a sys_id literal). This
         matches the convention established by the demo group's
         primary-key record at
         ../groups/sys_user_group_x_[scope]_demo_team.xml and the peer
         case records (cases 03-10).

      5. The case is visible to the demo agent under "Assigned only"
         via the GROUP-MEMBERSHIP CLAUSE only. When the demo agent
         impersonates and queries the case list, they see this case
         because they are a member of x_[scope]_demo_team (per the
         seed script's ensureGroupMembership helper). They do NOT see
         this case via the assigned_agent = current.sys_id clause
         (since assigned_agent is empty). This is the CANONICAL test
         for the SECOND clause of "Assigned only"; case 03 (and any
         other case with assigned_agent populated) is the canonical
         test for the FIRST clause.

      6. Demo case 02 has NO children in the demo dataset - no demo
         tasks, no demo parties. This is INTENTIONAL. Per the seed
         script's task and party tables, children are created only on
         cases that have been picked up by an agent (In Progress and
         beyond). This mirrors a realistic case lifecycle: tasks
         (sub-investigations) and parties (witnesses, respondents)
         are typically captured by the assigned agent during active
         investigation, not by the queue dispatcher at Draft/Open
         time.

      7. This case appears in:
           - the Open slice of the case_count_by_status donut
           - the Open bar of the all_cases_by_status bar chart
           - the General Inquiry slice of the all_cases_by_type donut
           - the Medium bar of the all_cases_by_priority bar chart
           - the count of the cases_opened_30d single-score widget
           (since opened_date is auto-set to "now" on insert by the
           set_opened_date business rule)
         This case does NOT appear in:
           - the avg_time_to_close widget (filters on status=Closed)
           - the demo agent's "My Open Cases" personal list
             (filter requires assigned_agent = current user, but
             assigned_agent is empty)

      8. The Draft -> Open transition USING this case as the post-
         transition state is testable. Sibling case 01 (Draft) is the
         pre-transition state; this case is the post-transition state.
         Together they form a paired demonstration of the Draft -> Open
         transition guard (validate_open_transition requires
         assigned_group populated). On case 01 at Draft, an attempt to
         transition to Open without populating assigned_group MUST be
         blocked. On this case (already Open with assigned_group set)
         the post-transition state is shown.

      9. The Open -> In Progress transition USING this case as the
         input is the canonical test in Validation Gate 2 (Workflow).
         When an operator (with case_manager or "Assigned only"
         case_agent role) attempts to set this case status to In
         Progress via the form WITHOUT first populating assigned_agent,
         the validate_inprogress_transition subflow MUST surface a
         form-level blocking error and the transition MUST be denied.
         After assigned_agent is populated on the form (selecting the
         demo agent, who is a member of x_[scope]_demo_team), the
         same transition attempt MUST succeed and yield case status =
         In Progress (matching the post-transition state of sibling
         case 03).

     10. The literal "[scope]" placeholder is preserved verbatim
         throughout the file - in the sys_class_name, sys_update_name,
         table attribute, inner element name, all cross-reference
         text values, and the file path. The PDI substitutes the
         auto-assigned concrete scope id at apply-time;
         pre-substituting here would break the substitution mechanism.
-->
